    "The central quest for the next decade in shrinking photonic chips and thus increasing density is to find the elusive 'ideal' modulator in silicon photonics-small in length (L), requiring a small drive voltage to incur a π phase shift (V π), offering low propagation loss (α) and IL, and for several applications, highly linear and with large -3 dB E/O bandwidth (BW) 49."
